text: "Which of the following is a criterion for classifying a vesicovaginal fistula as complication?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Location above the trigone", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Size is 4 cm", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "C", "text": "No prior radiation", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Normal vaginal length", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "* **Large vesicovaginal fistulas** are classified as complicated because they are technically difficult to repair and have a higher recurrence rate. \n* Size, location, prior radiation, and scarring influence management and prognosis.<br><br>\n* **A vesicovaginal fistula** is classified as complicated if it has features such as l**arge size (\u22653 cm)**, involvement of the trigone/urethra, prior radiation, malignancy, recurrent fistula, or associated vaginal scarring.",
