text: "Which hormone is primarily responsible for the growth of breast tissue?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Oxytocin", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Estrogen", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Prolactin", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Progesterone", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "The growth and development of mammary alveoli (as shown in the diagram) is primarily stimulated by progesterone. Progesterone is the primary hormone responsible for mammary alveolar growth and development, while estrogen primarily stimulates ductal growth. This hormonal distinction is crucial for understanding mammary gland development and the cyclical changes that occur during the menstrual cycle.<br><br>| **Hormone** | **Function** |\n| ------- | -------- |\n| **Estrogen** | Ductal growth of breast |\n| **Progesterone** | Lobuloalveolar development |\n| **Prolactin** | Milk production |\n| **Oxytocin** | Milk ejection (let-down reflex) |",
