explanation: "Pelvic adequacy is assessed using multiple pelvic diameters and overall obstetric assessment. Although the obstetric conjugate is important, a contracted pelvis cannot be defined by a single measurement alone. Clinical pelvimetry and labor outcome are also essential considerations.<br><br>A) True \u2014 The obstetric conjugate is the shortest AP diameter of the pelvic inlet.\nB) True \u2014 Diagonal conjugate is measured from the sacral promontory to the lower margin of the pubic symphysis on per vaginum exam.\nC) True \u2014 Obstetric conjugate \u2248 diagonal conjugate \u2212 1.5 cm.\nD)\u00a0 False \u2014 A contracted pelvis is defined when any pelvic diameter is reduced below normal size",
