explanation: "**Piper forceps** have long, curved shanks specifically designed to assist the **after-coming head in breech**.<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/a0327891-3de3-42a9-b03c-48422cd962f3.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">Wrigley = outlet forceps<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/b62d9ddb-f361-46ac-9a79-a3482dd4b46c.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">\nKielland = rotational forceps;\n<img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/a7caa850-cba5-4ec6-97db-3ed2830715d7.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">Dass = low forceps<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/9dd8e235-d23d-435b-a0d0-a4fe59b0ebbc.jpg\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
