explanation: "**Adenomyosis** is a condition where *endometrial tissue grows inside the uterine muscle (myometrium)*. This leads to:<br><br>* Diffuse uterine enlargement\n* Painful menstruation\n* Heavy menstrual bleeding<br><br>\n**Imaging Findings** (TVS)<br><br>* Heterogeneous myometrium\n* Myometrial cysts\n* Globular uterus<br><br>\n**MRI** *may show junctional zone thickening (>12 mm).*",
